            <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Before you start </h1>
            <p class="govuk-body"><strong>You will need to decide the approach and stages to your procurement. These may include:</strong></p>

<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
<li><strong>Request for Information (RfI):</strong> this is used to gather market intelligence on similar projects scope, duration and learning from other projects</li>
<li><strong>Call-off Further Competition Capability Assessment:</strong> this is used to ask key questions of suppliers with a view to identifying a smaller number of suppliers</li>
<li><strong>Call-off Further Competition:</strong> this is used to compare the relative merits of the shortlisted suppliers tender responses based on an evaluation of qualitative, commercial and social value criteria</li>
</ul>
<br>
<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">To buy from this lot you will need to follow the steps below: </h3><h3>

    <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
        <li>
          <h3 class="proc-task-list__section">
            
             Take a look at the available suppliers
          </h3>

          <p class="govuk-body">Every supplier is checked to make sure they can supply the products or services offered by the commercial agreement. You can sort them by:
          </p> 
          <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
